WORKING debmirror command for RHEL10 (EPEL version)
Code
debmirror \
  -a amd64 \
  -d trixie,trixie-updates,trixie-security \
  -s main \
  -h deb.debian.org \
  -r debian \
  --method=http \
  --progress \
  /var/www/html/repos/debian13
This WILL run.
This is the correct syntax for the RHEL/EPEL version.

Let me break down each option:

Option	Meaning
-a amd64	architecture
-d trixie,trixie-updates,trixie-security	distributions
-s main	section
-h deb.debian.org	host
-r debian	root path
--method=http	protocol
--progress	show progress
/var/www/html/repos/debian13	required final argument (mirror directory)


If you leave off the final directory, debmirror complains that every option “requires an argument.”

✔ If you want a config file, you CAN still use one
…but you must source it yourself and pass the values manually.

Example:

/etc/debmirror/debian13.conf
Code
ARCH=amd64
DIST="trixie,trixie-updates,trixie-security"
SECTION=main
HOST=deb.debian.org
ROOT=debian
METHOD=http
MIRROR=/var/www/html/repos/debian13
Wrapper script /usr/local/bin/sync-debian13.sh
Code
#!/bin/bash
source /etc/debmirror/debian13.conf

debmirror \
  -a "$ARCH" \
  -d "$DIST" \
  -s "$SECTION" \
  -h "$HOST" \
  -r "$ROOT" \
  --method="$METHOD" \
  --progress \
  "$MIRROR"
Make executable:

Code
chmod +x /usr/local/bin/sync-debian13.sh
Run:

Code
/usr/local/bin/sync-debian13.sh
This avoids the “requires an argument” errors because:

every option has a value

the mirror directory is passed last

no unsupported long options are used
